Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:CSO 

  [Text] IRNA-- During an armed clash between the law 
enforcement personnel of Tayebad and outlaws and narcotics 
smugglers north of the city of Khaf, 714 kg of opium was seized. 
  The public relations office of Khorasan law enforcement 
reported: Clashes occurred over the past two days in three chase 
operations in the Mebraq and Siah Darreh Heights. 
  Following these clashes, the smugglers escaped, but one of 
them, who is an Afghan citizen, was arrested. 
  Early this week also, 548 kg of opium were seized in an 
armed 
clash in the Ahangaran Heights. 

